{"tid":2294891,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"威斯康星州重新點票 , 檢票委員會仍拒絕剔除沒填寫個人資料的缺席投票","createTime":"2020-11-21T10:50:37.000Z","updateTime":"2020-11-21T13:12:00.000Z","uid":25468,"like":2,"dislike":19,"uniUserReply":20,"replies":[{"pid":"5b9e9691a27264d7002169ae487ff9f2e4b87b45","tid":2294891,"uid":25468,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-21T10:50:37.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.newsmax.com/us/election-2020-wisconsin-recount/2020/11/20/id/998118/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsmax.com%2Fus%2Felection-2020-wisconsin-recount%2F2020%2F11%2F20%2Fid%2F998118%2F&d=HaoFMq3H8OfxnxI562yM3yNFMfcMnrnh95DLK%2BYL5kQ%3D&h=bcbfe4bd\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.newsmax.com/us/election-2020-wisconsin-recount/2020/11/20/id/998118/</a><br />\n<br />\nThe recount of the presidential election in Wisconsin&rsquo;s two most heavily Democratic counties began Friday with President Donald Trump&rsquo;s campaign seeking to discard tens of thousands of absentee ballots that it alleged should not have been counted.<br />\n<br />\nTrump&rsquo;s three objections attempting to discard the ballots were denied by the three-member Dane County Board of Canvassers, twice on bipartisan votes. Dane County Clerk Scott McDonell said he expected the campaign was building a record before filing a lawsuit.<br />\n<br />\nJoe Biden won Wisconsin by 20,600 votes and carried Dane and Milwaukee counties by a 2-to-1 margin. Trump only paid for recounts in those two counties, not in the 70 others, 58 of which he won.<br />\n<br />\nThere's no precedent for a recount overturning a deficit as large as Trump's in Wisconsin, so his strategy is widely seen as seeking to build a case to take to court.<br />\n<br />\nHis team on Friday sought to have ballots discarded where election clerks filled in missing address information on the certification envelope where the ballot is inserted; any absentee ballot where a voter declared themselves to be &ldquo;indefinitely confined&rdquo; under the law; and any absentee ballot where there was not a written application on file, including roughly 69,000 that were cast in-person during the two weeks before Election Day.<br />\n<br />\nTrump attorney Christ Troupis argued that certification envelopes filled out by people who voted absentee in-person do not count under the law as a written application, even though the envelope is identified as such. The board of canvassers, controlled 2-1 by Democrats, voted unanimously to reject the complaint.<br />\n<br />\nTroupis also argued that people claimed to be indefinitely confined even though they were not. Such a declaration exempts the voter from having to show a photo ID to cast their ballot, which Troupis called &ldquo;an open invitation for fraud and abuse.&rdquo; The Republican-controlled Wisconsin Supreme Court this spring ruled that it is up to individual voters to determine whether they are indefinitely confined, in line with guidance from the bipartisan Wisconsin Elections Commission.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n檢票委員會由2個民主黨員+1個共和黨員組成 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b6202e2016930a8ab9f5568656764df30750bc24","tid":2294891,"uid":183758,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-21T10:52:09.000Z","msg":"共匪民主黨一定要徹底肅清"},{"pid":"b016531fd916703d3c80a3f24da7e0c3cf101e5b","tid":2294891,"uid":21545,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-21T10:54:19.000Z","msg":"咁都計<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"42be3e07fa5f5b3e027722f18ed165b2cd953055","tid":2294891,"uid":199893,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-11-21T10:55:01.000Z","msg":"咁咪即係亂寫到計<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d255533ffaa9b50ad21971d558688e0d6514e519","